<component type="desktop-application">
  <id>org.davidedmundson.kiot</id>
  
  <name>Kiot</name>
  <summary>KDE Internet of Things: desktop integration for Home Automation</summary>
  
  <metadata_license>FSFAP</metadata_license>
  <project_license>LGPL-2.1-or-later</project_license>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      Kiot is a background daemon that bridges your KDE desktop session with home automation platforms like Home Assistant. 
      It exposes device sensors, system information, and controls, allowing your home automation system to interact seamlessly 
      with your local environment.
    </p>
    <p>
      With Kiot, you can:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Monitor system status </li>
      <li>Control media players via MPRIS</li>
      <li>Manage Docker containers</li>
      <li>Control systemd services</li>
      <li>Launch games from Steam/Heroic</li>
      <li>Send notifications to your desktop</li>
      <li>Track active window and user activity</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      All data is exposed via MQTT to Home Assistant, where you can create powerful automations that integrate your desktop with your smart home.
    </p>
  </description>
  
